---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const updated = 'June 15, 2025';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service" description="BrandedBikers terms of service for brands, campaign clients, and rider network participants.">

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="section-title">TERMS OF <span>SERVICE</span></h1>
      <p>Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container legal-body">

      <p class="lead">These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of BrandedBikers services, including our website, rider program, and campaign platform. By using our services, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use our services.</p>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. Definitions</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>"BrandedBikers," "we," "us," "our"</strong> — BrandedBikers and its operators.</li>
          <li><strong>"Client"</strong> — a brand or company that commissions a marketing campaign through BrandedBikers.</li>
          <li><strong>"Rider"</strong> — an individual who participates in a BrandedBikers campaign as a brand ambassador.</li>
          <li><strong>"Campaign"</strong> — a defined marketing engagement in which riders wear and represent a client's branded gear over a specified period.</li>
          <li><strong>"Submission"</strong> — mileage records, route documentation, and photographs provided by a rider as campaign deliverables.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>You must be at least 18 years old to use our services. By using our services, you represent that you meet this requirement and have the authority to agree to these Terms.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. Campaign Clients</h2>
        <h3>Campaign agreements</h3>
        <p>Clients who engage BrandedBikers for a campaign will enter into a separate Campaign Agreement that specifies deliverables, pricing, timeline, and payment terms. These Terms apply in addition to that agreement.</p>
        <h3>Payment</h3>
        <p>Campaign fees are due per the schedule outlined in your Campaign Agreement. Late payments may result in campaign suspension. All fees are non-refundable except as explicitly stated in your Campaign Agreement.</p>
        <h3>Use of deliverables</h3>
        <p>Photos and rider-generated content provided in campaign reports are licensed to the client for marketing use in connection with the campaign. Clients may not use rider likenesses in ways that imply endorsement beyond the scope of the campaign without separate written consent from BrandedBikers and the rider.</p>
        <h3>No guarantee of specific results</h3>
        <p>BrandedBikers guarantees verified deliverables (documented rides, miles, and photos). We do not guarantee specific sales outcomes, impressions, or business results from a campaign.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Riders</h2>
        <h3>Program participation</h3>
        <p>Riders participate in campaigns subject to the BrandedBikers Rider Program Handbook, which is incorporated into these Terms. By joining a campaign, you agree to the Handbook's rules and submission requirements.</p>
        <h3>Honesty and accuracy</h3>
        <p>Riders must provide accurate mileage, route, and photo submissions. Fabricating, falsifying, or misrepresenting any submission is grounds for immediate removal from the network and forfeiture of compensation. BrandedBikers reserves the right to pursue legal remedies if a client is materially damaged by fraudulent submissions.</p>
        <h3>Conduct</h3>
        <p>Riders are expected to conduct themselves in accordance with the campaign's brand standards at all times while wearing or publicly representing branded gear. Conduct that brings the client's brand into disrepute may result in removal from the campaign and forfeiture of compensation.</p>
        <h3>Intellectual property</h3>
        <p>By submitting photos and content to BrandedBikers, riders grant BrandedBikers and the applicable campaign client a non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use submitted content for campaign reporting and marketing purposes. Riders retain ownership of their original content.</p>
        <h3>Compensation</h3>
        <p>Rider compensation is specified in individual campaign agreements. BrandedBikers is not responsible for compensation disputes arising from late, incomplete, or unverifiable submissions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Prohibited Conduct</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Submit false, fabricated, or misleading mileage, route, or photo data</li>
          <li>Impersonate any person or entity</li>
          <li>Use our services for any unlawful purpose</li>
          <li>Interfere with or disrupt our website or services</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of our systems</li>
          <li>Engage in conduct that damages the reputation of BrandedBikers or any campaign client</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All content on this website — including text, graphics, logos, and design — is owned by or licensed to BrandedBikers and is protected by applicable intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works without our prior written consent.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>Our services are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied. We do not warrant that the website will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of viruses. BrandedBikers disclaims all warranties to the fullest extent permitted by law.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, BrandedBikers shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of our services, even if we have been advised of the possibility of such damages. Our total liability for any claim shall not exceed the amount you paid us in the three months preceding the claim.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>You agree to indemnify and hold BrandedBikers harmless from any claims, damages, losses, or costs (including attorneys' fees) arising from your use of our services, your violation of these Terms, or your violation of any rights of another party.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Termination</h2>
        <p>We may suspend or terminate your access to our services at any time for violation of these Terms or for any other reason at our discretion. Riders who violate the Rider Handbook are subject to immediate removal and forfeiture of outstanding compensation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the United States and the state in which BrandedBikers operates, without regard to conflict of law principles. Any disputes shall be resolved in the appropriate courts of that jurisdiction.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>12. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>We may update these Terms at any time. Updated Terms will be posted with a revised "Last updated" date. Continued use of our services after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>13. Contact</h2>
        <p>For questions about these Terms, contact us at:</p>
        <div class="contact-block">
          <p><strong>BrandedBikers</strong></p>
          <p><a href="mailto:info@brandedbikers.com">info@brandedbikers.com</a></p>
          <p><a href="https://www.brandedbikers.com">www.brandedbikers.com</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-body { max-width: 760px; padding-bottom: 4rem; }

  .lead {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--white);
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .legal-section p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-section li { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; }

  .legal-section a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline; }

  .contact-block {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }

  .contact-block p { margin: 0; color: var(--text); }
  .contact-block a { color: var(--accent); }
</style>
